    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "For anyone landing here while searching… There is another way — custom widgets. Inspired by https://stackoverflow.com/a/42674116/3082178.\r\n\r\nIn InstantSearch v4 it looks like this:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nsearch.addWidgets([\r\n  {\r\n    $$type: 'Playlist manager',\r\n    render: ({ results }) => {\r\n      console.log(results);\r\n    },\r\n  },\r\n]);\r\n```\r\n\r\nP.S.\r\n@jamesfzhang I have faced the same use case, ability to autoplay the next song when the first one finishes in the search results.\r\n",
    "created_at": "2024-03-17T15:38:28Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/953#issuecomment-2002512390",
